  // ── TRANSITION B (shape intro) fires here (after index 12, before index 13) ──

  // ── 14 SHAPE MC  warm-up: 4 circles = 20
  { type:'mc', floor:'Floor Fourteen', name:'The Cipher Gallery',
    story:'The alchemist leads you into a gallery lined with glowing symbols. "No letters here," they say. "Just shapes. Each shape hides a value — your job is the same as always: make the scale balance." They point to the scale. In the left pan: four circles, each weighing the same. In the right: 20.',
    lp:'🔵 🔵 🔵 🔵', rp:'20',
    q:'Each 🔵 weighs the same amount. What does one circle weigh?',
    ans:['4','5','6','7'], cor:1,
    exp:'✓  20 ÷ 4 = 5. Each circle weighs 5. An easy start — the gallery door swings open!'
  },
  // ── 15 SHAPE MC  two shapes: 2 circles + 1 square = 16, square=4
  { type:'mc', floor:'Floor Fifteen', name:'The Cipher Gallery II',
    story:'A second scale. This time both pans hold two different shapes. A small card pinned to the scale reads: "Each 🟧 weighs 4." The left pan holds 2 circles and 1 square. The right pan holds 16. You need to find the weight of one circle.',
